## Output Contract

Write `idea.md` with this exact structure:

## Strategy
(1-2 sentence thesis: what we are trying and why we expect it to improve the score)

## Modification

### What to change
(Exact files in `discovered/`, exact functions, exact code changes)

### Why this should work
(Technical reasoning: how this changes learning dynamics or optimization)

## Executor Freedom
(Only narrow tuning choices the executor may make; everything else is fixed)

## Implementation Plan
(Numbered steps: what to modify in which `discovered/` file, in what order)

## Pitfalls to Watch
(Known failure modes, numerical stability, interface violations)

Rules: be specific, preserve function signatures/interfaces, and keep each idea
to one mechanism across 1-2 `discovered/` files.

Update `memory.md` first, then write `idea.md`.
